Package de.yamass.redg.generator.extractor

Class TableExtractor

java.lang.Object
de.yamass.redg.generator.extractor.TableExtractor
public class TableExtractor extends Object
This class provides methods to extract a TableModel from a Table. It offers static methods for dealing with join tables as well.

    • TableExtractor

      public TableExtractor(String classPrefix, String targetPackage, DataTypeProvider dataTypeProvider, NameProvider nameProvider, ExplicitAttributeDecider explicitAttributeDecider, ConvenienceSetterProvider convenienceSetterProvider)
      Creates a new table extractor with the specified class prefix and the specified target package.
      Parameters:
      classPrefix - The prefix to put before class names. Only a-zA-Z, starting with a capital letter
      targetPackage - The target package. Usage of default package is forbidden.
      dataTypeProvider - The DataTypeProvider to read the data types from. If null defaults to DefaultDataTypeProvider.
      explicitAttributeDecider - The ExplicitAttributeDecider that decides whether an attribute or foreign key is "explicit" or not. If null defaults to DefaultExplicitAttributeDecider.
      nameProvider - The NameProvider that provides the class, field and method names for the generated code. If null defaults to DefaultNameProvider.
      convenienceSetterProvider - The ConvenienceSetterProvider that returns information about wanted convenience setters. If null defaults to DefaultConvenienceSetterProvider.

  • Method Details

    • extractTableModel

      public TableModel extractTableModel(schemacrawler.schema.Table table)
      Extracts the table model from a single table. Every table this table references via foreign keys must be fully loaded, otherwise an exception will be thrown.
      Parameters:
      table - The table to extract the model from
      Returns:
      The extracted model with all information needed for code generation

    • isJoinTable

      public static boolean isJoinTable(schemacrawler.schema.Table table)
      Uses heuristics to determine whether a table is a join table.

      A table is identified as a join table if every column is part of a foreign key or part of the primary key. Furthermore the primary may only consist of a single column or every column has to be part of a foreign key.

      Parameters:
      table - The table to check
      Returns:
      true if the table is probably a join table, false otherwise

    • analyzeJoinTable

      public static Map<String,Map<schemacrawler.schema.Table,List<String>>> analyzeJoinTable(schemacrawler.schema.Table table)
      Analyzes a join table and returns information about the foreign key relationships in this table

      Example:

      If the passed table is table ABC that is a join table for the m:n:o relation between tables A, B and C, the method will return 

           - A :
          - ABC :
                 - B
                 - C
     - B :
          - ABC :
                 - A
                 - C
     - C :
          - ABC :
                 - A
                 - B
      This information should be read as "A has a relation to B and C via the table ABC" and so on
      Parameters:
      table - The table to analyze
      Returns:
      The information about the join table. See method description for format details.
